<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 61; Nasdaq Climbs 89  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 61 points
in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a nearly 2-1 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 89 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up seven points.
</P>
<P>
   Markets should be little affected by this morning's labor
report.
</P>
<P>
   That's because the numbers were pretty close to expectations.
</P>
<P>
   And analysts say they'll do little to change the Federal
Reserve's mind about the continuing need to raise interest rates to
keep inflation contained.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are narrowly mixed.
</P>
