<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Accused in Harrison Attack Held  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OXFORD, England (AP) -- The man accused of stabbing George
Harrison and wounding the ex-Beatle's wife, was ordered back to a
psychiatric unit Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Abram, 33, of Liverpool, spoke only to confirm his
identity and that he understood the charges during a brief court
hearing.
</P>
<P>
   The court ordered Abram detained at the Scott Clinic outside
Liverpool in northern England, a medium security unit where he has
been under observation.
</P>
<P>
   Abram is charged with the attempted murder in an attack on
Harrison, 56, and his wife Olivia, 51, at their home in
Henley-on-Thames, west of London, on Dec. 31.
</P>
<P>
   George Harrison reportedly fought off his attacker and received
slash injuries and a one-inch stab wound that collapsed his right
lung.
</P>
<P>
   His wife was scratched and bruised in the attack, which
rekindled memories of the murder of fellow Beatle John Lennon. In
1980, Lennon was shot to death in New York City by a deranged fan.
</P>
<P>
   The magistrates ordered another hearing on May 12.
</P>
</TEXT>
